    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix race condition in ue_context_modification_confirm leading to potential segfault\n\n### Summary\nThe `ue_context_modification_confirm` function in the MAC layer releases the scheduler lock before calling `nr_rlc_srb_recv_sdu`, creating a race condition where the UE context can be freed by another thread between these operations. This can lead to accessing freed memory and cause segmentation faults under load.\n\nThis fix ensures the scheduler lock is held during the entire critical section.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/mac_rrc_dl_handler.c`: Moved `NR_SCHED_UNLOCK` to occur after `nr_rlc_srb_recv_sdu` call in `ue_context_modification_confirm`\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder high UE churn conditions with frequent context modifications, observe intermittent segmentation faults in the RLC layer when processing SRB data. The crash occurs in `nr_rlc_srb_recv_sdu` when accessing UE context that was freed by another thread after the lock was released but before the RLC operation completed.\n\n"
}